Take the plunge.

00:38:23.890 --> 00:38:24.890
ASHLEY CHANG: Daron, OK.

00:38:24.890 --> 00:38:26.220
Now, we talked about Durant.

00:38:26.220 --> 00:38:29.630
Now, our other favorite
topic-- donuts, right?

00:38:29.630 --> 00:38:32.720
What is with you
and donuts, and what

00:38:32.720 --> 00:38:35.150
is with this donut council?

00:38:35.150 --> 00:38:40.040
DARON ROBERTS: So
I realized that I

00:38:40.040 --> 00:38:42.980
need to be very intentional
about spending time

00:38:42.980 --> 00:38:44.922
with my family.

00:38:44.922 --> 00:38:46.630
And I think a lot of
people say, oh, I'll

00:38:46.630 --> 00:38:50.009
spend more time with my family,
and then that's on a Sunday.

00:38:50.009 --> 00:38:51.550
And then you get to
Saturday, and you

00:38:51.550 --> 00:38:54.790
think, oh, I haven't spent any
time with my family, right?

00:38:54.790 --> 00:38:59.414
So I went into Google
Calendar, and--

00:38:59.414 --> 00:39:01.330
ASHLEY CHANG: We haven't
even talked about it.

00:39:01.330 --> 00:39:02.050
This is great.

00:39:02.050 --> 00:39:03.024
We should have you come back.

00:39:03.024 --> 00:39:03.990
Are you free next week?

00:39:03.990 --> 00:39:05.560
DARON ROBERTS: Yeah, of course.

00:39:05.560 --> 00:39:08.980
Just kind of up the temperature
level a little bit outside.

00:39:08.980 --> 00:39:12.410
So my family's color
code is orange.

00:39:12.410 --> 00:39:18.710
And we have every Saturday,
7:30, I take the kids,

00:39:18.710 --> 00:39:21.392
and we go to a different
donut shop in Austin.

00:39:21.392 --> 00:39:23.350
ASHLEY CHANG: And you
said there were how many?

00:39:23.350 --> 00:39:24.922
DARON ROBERTS: There are 38.

00:39:24.922 --> 00:39:26.630
ASHLEY CHANG: Is that
more than New York?

00:39:26.630 --> 00:39:27.760
DARON ROBERTS: It's crazy.

00:39:27.760 --> 00:39:29.330
It's crazy.

00:39:29.330 --> 00:39:32.160
And what's happened-- this has
been going on for four years.

00:39:32.160 --> 00:39:35.915
My mom does embroidery,
so we've got T-shirts.

00:39:35.915 --> 00:39:38.040
We walk in, and people are
like, oh, Donut Council.

00:39:38.040 --> 00:39:38.930
Hey.

00:39:38.930 --> 00:39:41.359
Comp you a few donuts,
be sure to post.

00:39:41.359 --> 00:39:43.400
ASHLEY CHANG: That's how
you ask for free things.

00:39:43.400 --> 00:39:44.477
Just wear the shirt.

00:39:44.477 --> 00:39:45.310
DARON ROBERTS: Yeah.

00:39:45.310 --> 00:39:47.990
And now it's gotten
to the point where

00:39:47.990 --> 00:39:53.960
my kids are kind of becoming
snobs in a sense of--

00:39:53.960 --> 00:39:56.750
my daughter last
week, we were a place.

00:39:56.750 --> 00:40:00.682
She goes, you know, cinnamon
rolls here are a bit dry.

00:40:00.682 --> 00:40:02.390
ASHLEY CHANG: And
which daughter is this?

00:40:02.390 --> 00:40:03.180
How old is she.

00:40:03.180 --> 00:40:03.460
DARON ROBERTS: Sydney.

00:40:03.460 --> 00:40:03.820
Sydney's five.

00:40:03.820 --> 00:40:05.070
I'm like, Sydney, you're five.

00:40:05.070 --> 00:40:06.355
Just eat the damn thing.

00:40:06.355 --> 00:40:07.730
ASHLEY CHANG: But
Dad, it's not--

00:40:07.730 --> 00:40:08.450
DARON ROBERTS: She's
like, it's not as moist.

00:40:08.450 --> 00:40:10.120
This donut hole they have--

00:40:10.120 --> 00:40:12.170
just eat.

00:40:12.170 --> 00:40:14.400
Now I'm spending
a small mortgage.

00:40:14.400 --> 00:40:18.560
It started out, oh, half
a dozen donut holes here.

00:40:18.560 --> 00:40:20.250
Have fun.

00:40:20.250 --> 00:40:23.449
People want bear claws
and chocolate sprinkles.

00:40:23.449 --> 00:40:25.990
ASHLEY CHANG: Well, and it start
off with how many, and now--

00:40:25.990 --> 00:40:26.600
DARON ROBERTS: So yeah.

00:40:26.600 --> 00:40:27.683
It started off with three.

00:40:27.683 --> 00:40:28.680
Now we have five.

00:40:28.680 --> 00:40:29.930
ASHLEY CHANG: Congratulations.

00:40:29.930 --> 00:40:31.720
I know your youngest is
seven months, rights?

00:40:31.720 --> 00:40:33.386
DARON ROBERTS:
[INAUDIBLE] seven months,

00:40:33.386 --> 00:40:36.137
and he's just trying to
get some of the residue

00:40:36.137 --> 00:40:36.970
from the donut hole.

00:40:36.970 --> 00:40:39.900
He's just kind of
licking himself.

00:40:39.900 --> 00:40:41.310
But it's also a great time for--

00:40:41.310 --> 00:40:45.950
I get back with him around
11:00 so my wife can just go

00:40:45.950 --> 00:40:48.320
and be childless for a while.

00:40:48.320 --> 00:40:51.990
She works for a nonprofit
and also helps with kids,

00:40:51.990 --> 00:40:54.770
and so it's good to kind
of give her some space.

00:40:54.770 --> 00:40:57.600
But we're at it for four
years, and it's been fun.

00:40:57.600 --> 00:41:01.029
So if anyone wants to donate
to the Donut Council--

00:41:01.029 --> 00:41:02.570
ASHLEY CHANG: Half
a million dollars?

00:41:02.570 --> 00:41:03.140
DARON ROBERTS: Half
a million dollars

00:41:03.140 --> 00:41:04.349
will go a hell of a long way.

00:41:04.349 --> 00:41:06.098
ASHLEY CHANG: How many
donuts can you eat?

00:41:06.098 --> 00:41:07.840
Maybe with the bear
claws it'd be less.

00:41:07.840 --> 00:41:09.798
DARON ROBERTS: Yeah,
yeah, with the bear claws.

